\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

An Eppley Laboratory, Inc., pyranometer measures short-wave irradiance.
 The dome normally used is UG295 glass, which gives wide coverage of the
 solar spectrum (from 0.285 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu m$
\end_inset

 to 2.8 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu m$
\end_inset

).
 Different bandwidths can be obtained by use of different glass domes, available
 from RAF upon request.
 (See Bulletin No.
 25.) The pyranometers are usually flown in pairs, one up-looking and one
 down-looking.
 They are calibrated periodically at the NOAA Solar Radiation Facility in
 Boulder, Colorado.
 The x denotes either bottom (B) or top (T).
\end_layout

