This is a complex calculation of the astronomical measurement of solar declinati
on angle, the angular distance of the sun north or south of the earth's
 equator.
 (Positive values are north.) It also makes a complex calculation of solar
 hour angle that takes leap year into account.
 The calculations were adapted by Ron Ruth from a FORTRAN program used by
 Lutz Bannehr.
